    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I assume <code>P</code> is also meant to be invariant under isomorphism, and probably <code>P 0</code> should hold, and maybe you want to assume something about direct sums too?<br>\nI tend to assume it's better to state things like <code>cone_mem</code> in the form \"for every distinguished triangle <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Z</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\to Y \\to Z</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span></span></span></span>, <code>P X -&gt; P Y -&gt; P Z</code>\" rather than making some arbitrary (but useless) choice of \"the\" cone, and then having to invoke isomorphism invariance</p>",
        "id": 265955102,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1640295115
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(e.g. compare \"a pushout of a cofibration is a cofibration\" <a href=\"https://github.com/rwbarton/lean-homotopy-theory/blob/lean-3.4.2/src/homotopy_theory/formal/cofibrations/cofibration_category.lean#L55-L56\">https://github.com/rwbarton/lean-homotopy-theory/blob/lean-3.4.2/src/homotopy_theory/formal/cofibrations/cofibration_category.lean#L55-L56</a>)</p>",
        "id": 265955339,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1640295338
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Since </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">id</mi><mo>⁡</mo></mrow><mi>X</mi></msub></mover></mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>→</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\overset{\\operatorname{id}_X}{\\to} X \\to 0 \\to X[1]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1643em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.1643em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.5782em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mop mtight\"><span class=\"mop mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathrm mtight\">id</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3448em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.3567em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1433em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>is a triangle, you get <code>P 0</code> from <code>P (cone T f)</code>.  </p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110032\">Reid Barton</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/116395-maths/topic/semiorthogonal.20decompositions/near/265955102\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I assume <code>P</code> is also meant to be invariant under isomorphism,</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Should it? It seems to fall in the same space as full vs strictly full subcategories. </p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110032\">Reid Barton</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/116395-maths/topic/semiorthogonal.20decompositions/near/265955102\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I tend to assume it's better to state things like <code>cone_mem</code> in the form \"for every distinguished triangle <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Z</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\to Y \\to Z</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span></span></span></span>, <code>P X -&gt; P Y -&gt; P Z</code>\" rather than making some arbitrary (but useless) choice of \"the\" cone, and then having to invoke isomorphism invariance</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, this is very good advice. Thanks.</p>",
