        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1640295359
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"306577\">Matthew Ballard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/116395-maths/topic/semiorthogonal.20decompositions/near/265955351\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Since </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">id</mi><mo>⁡</mo></mrow><mi>X</mi></msub></mover></mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>→</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\overset{\\operatorname{id}_X}{\\to} X \\to 0 \\to X[1]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1643em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.1643em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.5782em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mop mtight\"><span class=\"mop mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathrm mtight\">id</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3448em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.3567em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1433em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>is a triangle, you get <code>P 0</code> from <code>P (cone T f)</code>.  </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>but <code>P</code> might not hold for any object to start with!</p>",
        "id": 265955412,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1640295386
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah yes <span aria-label=\"embarrassed\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f633\" role=\"img\" title=\"embarrassed\">:embarrassed:</span></p>",
        "id": 265955432,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1640295414
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If <code>P</code> is closed under cofibers then it is also closed under replacing objects by isomorphic ones (since <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>→</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi>X</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0 \\to X \\to X&#x27;</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is distinguished if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi>X</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\to X&#x27;</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is an iso)</p>",
        "id": 265955450,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1640295444
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In other words if you rephrase <code>cone_mem</code> in the style I suggested then isomorphism invariance is a consequence (once you have <code>P 0</code>). If you ask for it to be closed under forming \"the\" cone then it's a weird concept if you did not already assume it to be isomorphism invariant.</p>",
        "id": 265955548,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1640295516
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I agree</p>",
        "id": 265955559,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1640295529
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>About direct sums, you want to prove some results about (co)limits and left/right orthogonals. Is it valuable to package some assumptions directly?</p>",
        "id": 265955685,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1640295687
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"306577\">@Matthew Ballard</span> It will be very interesting to hear if you find the current setup of pretriangulated categories pleasant to work with. My gut feeling is that there might be too much bundling of triangles, and that this might be annoying to work with in practice.</p>",
